The paper deals with improving the robustness of machine comprehension models through adversarial training, which is a common topic in natural language processing (NLP) and machine learning (ML) research. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). Additionally, the paper proposes a novel algorithm for generating adversarial examples, which involves improving the model's semantic-relationship learning capabilities, suggesting that it could also fall under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also mentions using convolutional neural networks (CNNs) for feature extraction, which could place it under cs.CV (Computer Vision). Finally, the paper uses reinforcement learning to improve the model's performance, which could place it under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
